<div class="spacer"></div>

<p>Through the ages, plaid has proved its flexibility in design. From the days of tartan wool to todays plaid patterns, it has evolved into a fascinating modern marvel. While the plaid pattern itself was originally known as tartan, over time the two names became synonamous and by the time the pattern became popular in America it was known by plaid. Though the two names are still interchangable, many have fallen under the belief that plaid represents the pattern while tartan is what Scottish kilts are made of. Regardless, the pattern itself is a wonder in design. </p>
