<p>Often considered an exclusively classic pattern, lately plaid has become more courageous and bold, finding its way into unconventional designs. From modern to contemporary, traditional to country, the plaid pattern has become a favorite within various design styles. Quiet and comforting, plaid has an innate ability to project a leisurely aura, bringing harmony to any space. Yet sporting unexpected colors and an impressive range of scale this classic is still as timeless as ever. </p>
